            <a href="HomeTest Operating Model - Persona Aisha.html" target="_blank">Aisha &middot; Clinical / CSG</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- STAGE 4 -->
    <div class="stage" id="stage-4">
      <div class="stage-side"><div class="stage-number">04</div></div>
      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">First home prescriptions &middot; Layla and the early cohort</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">Hannah picks the first patients carefully. Stable iron status, comfortable with the kit, the patients whose missed-appointment record is a logistics problem and not a clinical one. Layla is one of the first. The kit goes home, the result comes back, the diary slot stays free. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="hannah-s4"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image" style="padding:0;border:none;background:none;margin-bottom:22px;"><img src="Assets/Hannah Story/hannah-stage4.png" alt="Hannah Stage 4" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,32,64,0.12);"></div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">Patients I would already trust to manage their own monitoring if the tooling existed. Stable trend, comfortable with the kit, family at home if needed. The model meets Layla where she already is.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Hannah</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What the model is doing underneath</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">A short conversation at the end of the in-clinic appointment: would you be comfortable doing the next FBC at home? Almost every patient says yes. The kit ships via the framework supplier. The patient takes the sample on the date the clinic would have happened. The lab processes it. The result lands in Hannah&apos;s system on time. <strong>The clinic visit that did not happen is one the practice did not have capacity for anyway.</strong></div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Every patient comes in every six months. No tier of patients reading their own monitoring rhythm. No practice-nurse time freed for the patients who clinically need it. The clinic-only model treats every patient as if they need clinic time, regardless of whether they clinically do.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="careteam">
          <div class="careteam-icon">&#x1F465;</div>
          <div class="careteam-body">
            <div class="careteam-label">What the care team sees</div>
            <div class="careteam-text">The practice nurse coordinating onboarding. The supplier shipping the kit. The lab processing the sample. The framework platform writing the result back. The patient.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

