    <!-- STAGE 5 -->
    <div class="stage" id="stage-5">
      <div class="stage-side"><div class="stage-number">05</div></div>
      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">Routine monitoring in flight &middot; FBCs in the record, not in the diary</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">The cohort settles. Routine FBCs arrive on time, in trend, in the record. Threshold breaches escalate to her in the same channel she already uses. The practice diary is no longer the limit on how many patients she can hold in the cycle. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="hannah-s5"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image" style="padding:0;border:none;background:none;margin-bottom:22px;"><img src="Assets/Hannah Story/hannah-stage5.png" alt="Hannah Stage 5" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,32,64,0.12);"></div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">The silence is the result. Most of these results are routine, and routine is the point. When something does change, it changes on my screen with everything else around it, not three months later in a missed-appointment letter.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Hannah</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What the model is doing underneath</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">Routine in-range FBCs are reviewed in trend by Hannah in the same rhythm she would use for in-clinic results. Threshold breaches (haemoglobin, ferritin) trigger an alert and a routine review. Patients who would benefit from clinic come in; patients on a stable trend stay home for the next cycle. <strong>The system surfaces clinical signal, not appointment volume.</strong></div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Every six months, every patient, in clinic regardless of trend. Most appointments confirmed stability rather than detecting change. The clinically uneventful patients shared diary space with the patients who needed clinic, and the patients who needed clinic waited longer.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="careteam">
          <div class="careteam-icon">&#x1F465;</div>
          <div class="careteam-body">
            <div class="careteam-label">What the care team sees</div>
            <div class="careteam-text">Hannah, holding the trend review. The practice nurse, coordinating between routine and escalation. Priya on the platform data layer, ensuring the result writes back to the GP system cleanly. The patient.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="crosslinks">
          <div class="crosslinks-label">Where this lives in the model</div>
