    </div>

    <!-- STAGE 6 -->
    <div class="stage" id="stage-6">
      <div class="stage-side"><div class="stage-number">06</div></div>
      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">The practice shape now &middot; slots for the patients who need clinic</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">More patients in monitoring. Fewer drop-outs. The practice nurse&apos;s diary now holds the appointments that actually need her. Routine FBCs run quietly through the home pathway and the practice access-target line goes the right way for the first time in a long time. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="hannah-s6"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image" style="padding:0;border:none;background:none;margin-bottom:22px;"><img src="Assets/Hannah Story/hannah-stage6.png" alt="Hannah Stage 6" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,32,64,0.12);"></div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">The patients I worried about are still in the cycle. The practice nurse is doing work she should always have been doing. The bloods are happening on time. That is the version of this that was worth doing.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Hannah</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What the model is doing underneath</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">Cohort size on routine monitoring up. DNA rate on the routine-monitoring slot sharply down. Practice-nurse time reallocated from FBC draws to acute and complex appointments. Access-target performance on routine appointments improving. <strong>The same practice team holds more patients in monitoring than the clinic-only model could, with no extra clinic capacity.</strong> The model passes the test that mattered to Hannah: clinical accountability preserved, reach extended, practice nurse capacity returned.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Cohort size capped by practice capacity. DNA rates flat or rising. Practice-nurse phlebotomy slots consuming the workforce time the practice most needed for acute care. Routine monitoring patients silently dropping out of the cycle.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="careteam">
          <div class="careteam-icon">&#x1F465;</div>
          <div class="careteam-body">
            <div class="careteam-label">What the care team sees</div>
            <div class="careteam-text">Hannah and the practice nurse, holding a larger cohort with no extra diary cost. Anita, the ICB / GP commissioner, seeing released capacity flow into access metrics. Layla and the other patients on the cohort, getting on with their lives.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

